name: Jeba Diah
text: Pizza had been sitting for awhile, a bit soggy and only 2 choices. Restaurant was totally empty with the employee sitting in the back room. Tables not bussed. She took my order handed me the pizza and disappeared into the back. Never saw her again. For 5 bucks 2 slices wasn't too bad but don't think I'll go back.

text: Combo deals are a good price. Pizza by the slice is good, could be served hotter, I suppose I could've asked to have it heated in the oven. Salads are fresh. Sandwich was awesome, simple, but, fresh baguette, with good meat and cheese, excellent crunch.
